j": "drug", "prob": 0.9993027448654175, "span": {"begin": 511, "end": 520}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002118"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "calcium", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9996591806411743, "span": {"begin": 540, "end": 547}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:27637"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DomA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9942102432250977, "span": {"begin": 601, "end": 605}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2902"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "NMDARs", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9658073782920837, "span": {"begin": 644, "end": 650}}, {"id": ["mesh:C003121"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "glufosinate", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9982998967170715, "span": {"begin": 679, "end": 690}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2902"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "NMDARs", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.986682653427124, "span": {"begin": 691, "end": 697}}, {"id": ["mesh:C003121"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "glufosinate", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9979637861251831, "span": {"begin": 754, "end": 765}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2902"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "NMDARs", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9868473410606384, "span": {"begin": 773, "end": 779}}], "text": "NMDARs can be activated indirectly through initial activation of KA/AMPARs as it happens in the case of DomA exposure. DomA is an agonist of presynaptic and postsynaptic KARs and sustained activation of these receptors by DomA results in massive ion flux and excessive release of glutamate from excitatory terminals causing depolarization of the postsynaptic neuron (as descibed in MIE). Upon this depolarization the Mg2+ block is removed from the pore of NMDARs, resulting in their activation allowing sodium, potassium, and, importantly, calcium ions to enter into a cell. The sustained exposure to DomA causes pathological overactivation of NMDARs. In the case of exposure to glufosinate NMDARs activation is triggered by direct, sustained binding of glufosinate to the NMDARs.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:42:10 +0000 2026"}